5|$|Sharks can {{be highly}} social, {{remaining}} in large schools. Sometimes more than 100 <b>scalloped</b> <b>hammerheads</b> congregate around seamounts and islands, e.g., in the Gulf of California. Cross-species social hierarchies exist. For example, oceanic whitetip sharks dominate silky sharks of comparable size during feeding.|$|R
